<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-19T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-19T08:00:00-05:00" n="540" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/8: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-19T08:00:00-05:00">April 19, 1931—8
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>23. Your 60, April 18, 10 p.m., last paragraph. The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Memphis</hi> has been ordered to Ceiba. Inform
                            consuls.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
